title: Reinstalled League like 4 times and still don't have "lol.launcher.exe" or "lol.launcher.admin.exe"
body: I wonder if this is ever gonna be seen. Probably not. As the title says, I reinstalled League of Legends like 4 times and still don't have "lol.launcher.exe" or "lol.launcher.admin.exe". Looked everywhere. Feelsbadman.

replies.body:
Same, can't find it anywhere (custom install but i checked both the default and custom locations)

Trying to setup Wooxy but I don't have the file so I can't really do anything :/

If you installed League to the suggested default location, you should find it in C:\Riot Games\League of Legends and it should look something like this

https://i.gyazo.com/d813c3f9a219b71d49c6dd45ff91dad7.png
I'm not the OP, but a friend of mine is experiencing this same issue - neither of those files are in that folder for her, the only exe in that folder is LeagueClient.exe
Tried it, don't have it, uninstalled, reinstalled and still don't have it. Rinse and repeat. I probably have to do a clean sweep of my computer but it's not worth.
